<l>vēṟṟumaik kaṇṇu mataṉō raṟṟē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>It is said to be proper that in poetry</l>
<l>[it = the final <foreign xml:lang="ta">u</foreign>] is changed to <foreign xml:lang="ta">ā</foreign> when <foreign xml:lang="ta">aṉṟu</foreign> follows,</l>
<l>and disappears leaving the consonant when <foreign xml:lang="ta">ai</foreign> follows.<note place="foot">i.e., <foreign xml:lang="ta">atu + aṉṟu &gt; atāaṉṟu ; atu + ai &gt; atai.</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
